SIMPLE: inefficient
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Inefficient
<hw>In`ef*fi"cient</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Not
efficient; not producing the effect intended or desired, or achieving
the effect by unnecessary and excessive expenditure of resources;
inefficacious; <as>as, <ex>inefficient</ex> means or measures;
<ex>inefficient</ex> methods are too expensive</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Incapable of, or indisposed to, effective action;
habitually slack or remiss; effecting little or nothing; <as>as,
<ex>inefficient</ex> workmen; an <ex>inefficient</ex>
administrator.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Inefficiently</ent>⟦br⟧
